th Carolina at age thirty — four days short of his thirty-first birthday. His body was returned to New Haven Connecticut for burial at Grove Street Cemetery. The Charleston-to-New Haven body return tracks the established New England merchant-and-professional travel patterns of the period, when business interests took young New Englanders to southern coastal cities."},{"number":2,"category":"family","header":"Three young children at his death","body":"William Jr. left three young children at his 1817 death: Ann K. (age 5), Lavinia (already deceased as an infant in 1815), and Theodocia Pierpoint (born about a year before his death). His wife Nancy Kirby continued raising the surviving children before her own death in 1830 at age thirty-nine."}],"slug":"william-walter-jr-1786"},"I01295":{"id":"I01295","has_descendants_documented":false,"classification":{"include_in_path_calculation":true,"descent_from_thomas_hooker":false,"descent_from_john_talcott":false,"is_thomas_descendant":false,"is_talcott_descendant":false,"is_easter_egg":false},"parents":{},"tags":[],"sources":[],"marriages":[{"marriage_number":1,"spouse_id":"HD5102","children_ids":["HD5103","HD5104","HD5105"]}],"number_of_marriages":1,"notable":{"is_notable":false,"notable_category":[]},"birth":{"year":1791},"death":{"year":1830,"month":2,"day":10,"city":"New Haven","state":"Connecticut","country":"United States","age":39},"cross_connections":[],"bio":{"display_name":"Nancy Walter","first_name":"Nancy","last_name":"Walter","maiden_name":"Kirby","married_names":["Walter"],"gender":"female"},"residence":{},"baptism":{},"research_tags":[],"research_sources":[],"documents":[],"naming_inspiration":[],"institutions":[],"landmarks":[],"artworks":[],"quotes":[],"military_service":[],"slug":"nancy-kirby-1791"},"X01651":{"id":"X01651","has_descendants_documented":false,"classification":{"include_in_path_calculation":false,"descent_from_thomas_hooker":false,"descent_from_john_talcott":false,"is_thomas_descendant":false,"