sources":[],"documents":[],"naming_inspiration":[],"institutions":[],"landmarks":[],"artworks":[],"quotes":[],"military_service":[],"narrative_blocks":[{"number":1,"category":"death","header":"Daughter Louisa died thirty days after marriage","body":"Theodosia's daughter Louisa Walter married Timothy Bishop on April 3, 1800 — and died on May 3, 1800, just thirty days after the marriage. Louisa was twenty. The compressed marriage-and-death cycle within a single calendar month captured the period's vulnerability to acute disease across all socioeconomic groups, even within the Pierpont-Walter household at New Haven."},{"number":2,"category":"family","header":"Great-granddaughter named Theodocia Pierpont in her honor","body":"A generation after Theodosia's 1806 death, her son William Walter's daughter named her own daughter Theodocia Pierpont Walter Hayden (born August 20, 1817) — honoring the Pierpont great-grandmother through both first name and middle name. The naming carried the Theodosia-and-Pierpont identity forward across three generations of women in the family."},{"number":3,"category":"death","header":"Grandson William Walter Hayden drowned in childhood","body":"Theodosia's great-grandson William Walter Hayden — son of Theodocia Pierpont Walter Hayden — drowned on August 2, 1850 in Windsor Connecticut at age twelve. The cascading family losses — daughter at twenty in 1800, great-granddaughter at twenty in 1838, great-great-grandson at twelve in 1850 — touched four consecutive generations of the Walter-Hayden line."},{"number":4,"category":"family","header":"Born North Haven 1758, died New Haven 1806","body":"Theodosia Pierpont was born February 22, 1758 in North Haven Connecticut and died July 15, 1806 in New Haven Connecticut at age forty-eight. She married William Jay Walter on November 17, 1777 in North East Village, New Haven — he survived her by eighteen years, dying April 19, 1824. Her five documented children were Joel, Louisa, Lovina, Jerry, and William Jr."}],"slug":"theodosia-walter-1758"}},"burialCemetery":null,"institutionsById":{},"crossConnections":[]}